text: Haut-Uele (French for "Upper Uele") is one of the 26 provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo. Its capital is Isiro. It is named for the Uele River. Before 2015, Haut-Uele was part of Orientale Province. The territories in Haut-Uele are: * Dungu * Faradje * Niangara * Rungu * Wamba * Watsa ==References== Category:Provinces of the Democratic Republic of the Congo Category:2015 establishments in Africa
title: Haut-Uélé
